Confusion Matrix
  Work Done: Plotted confusion matrix to visualize performance.
Why/How: Shows true positives, true negatives, false positives, false negatives.
Learned: Visualization simplifies understanding of model errors.

Code:
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

cm = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues')
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.show()
Input & Prediction

Work Done: Created a text box for users to input messages and added a button to classify them.
Why/How: Real-time prediction demonstrates model functionality.
Learned: GUI integrates ML model with end-user interface.
  from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
import seaborn as sns
